---

<LegalLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Learn how AUXO Data Labs collects, uses, and protects your personal information in accordance with privacy regulations."
  lastUpdated="December 01, 2025"
>
  <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Welcome to AUXO Data Labs ("we," "us," "our"). We are a data analytics and intelligence company committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring your personal data is handled safely, lawfully, and transparently.</li>
    <li>This Policy applies to all users and visitors of our website, www.auxodata.com ("Site"), our clients, prospective clients, partners, and any other individuals whose personal data we process.</li>
    <li>We operate globally—including in the United Arab Emirates (UAE), the United States (US), and Europe—and comply with the UAE Personal Data Protection Law (PDPL), the EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), and relevant US state privacy laws such as the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA) and California Privacy Rights Act (CPRA).</li>
    <li>By visiting our Site or using our services, you acknowledge that you have read and understood this Policy.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>2. Data We Collect</h2>
  <h3>2.1 Personal Data You Provide</h3>
  <p>
    We collect personal data directly from you when you:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Complete a form on our Site (e.g., contact, demo request, or content download).</li>
    <li>Subscribe to newsletters or marketing communications.</li>
    <li>Engage with us at events or meetings.</li>
    <li>Apply for job opportunities.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Personal data may include:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Identifiers:</strong> Name, business email, telephone number.</li>
    <li><strong>Professional information:</strong> Job title, organization.</li>
    <li><strong>Other details:</strong> Feedback, inquiries, or information you choose to share.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>2.2 Data Collected Automatically</h3>
  <p>
    When you visit our Site, we may automatically collect:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Technical data:</strong> IP address, browser, operating system, device identifiers, session duration, navigation paths, and click-stream behaviour.</li>
    <li><strong>Geolocation data:</strong> Approximate location based on IP.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    This information is collected via cookies, web beacons, and similar technologies (see Section 4).
  </p>

  <h3>2.3 Data from Third Parties</h3>
  <p>
    We may receive personal data from:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Event or marketing partners:</strong> When you register for an event we sponsor.</li>
    <li><strong>Public sources:</strong> Such as LinkedIn, to identify potential business contacts.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. How We Use Your Data &amp; Legal Basis</h2>
  <p>
    We use your personal data for the following purposes and legal bases:
  </p>
  <table class="legal-table">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Purpose</th>
        <th>Legal Basis (GDPR / PDPL)</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Provide and maintain our Site and services.</td>
        <td>Contractual necessity; legitimate interest.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Respond to requests or inquiries.</td>
        <td>Consent; legitimate interest.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Send updates and marketing communications.</td>
        <td>Consent (withdrawable at any time).</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Analyze trends and improve our Site / services.</td>
        <td>Legitimate interest.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Prevent fraud, ensure security, and comply with law.</td>
        <td>Legal obligation; legitimate interest.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Personalize content and user experience.</td>
        <td>Legitimate interest.</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <p>
    We do not intentionally collect or process special categories of personal data unless provided with explicit consent.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Cookies &amp; Tracking Technologies</h2>
  <h3>4.1 What Are Cookies</h3>
  <p>
    Cookies are small text files placed on your device that help us operate and improve the Site.
  </p>

  <h3>4.2 How We Use Cookies</h3>
  <p>We use cookies to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Enable essential functionality (login, preferences).</li>
    <li>Measure Site performance and behaviour.</li>
    <li>Personalize content and marketing.</li>
    <li>Enhance security and fraud detection.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>4.3 Your Choices</h3>
  <p>
    On your first visit, a cookie banner lets you accept, reject, or manage preferences. You may adjust preferences anytime or disable cookies in your browser. Disabling certain cookies may affect website functionality.
  </p>

  <h3>4.4 Types of Cookies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Essential:</strong> Required for core functions.</li>
    <li><strong>Analytics / Performance:</strong> Measure usage to improve the Site.</li>
    <li><strong>Marketing / Advertising:</strong> Deliver relevant ads and track effectiveness.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    See the <a href={createUrl("legal/cookie-policy")}>Cookie Policy</a> for detailed information.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Disclosure of Your Data</h2>
  <p>
    We may share data:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>With service providers (hosting, analytics, marketing) under strict confidentiality.</li>
    <li>With affiliates or subsidiaries for legitimate business purposes.</li>
    <li>To comply with legal obligations or protect rights.</li>
    <li>As part of a business transaction (merger, acquisition, etc.).</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    <strong>We do not sell or trade personal data.</strong>
  </p>
  <p>
    We do not intentionally collect or process sensitive personal data (such as health, biometric, religious, or political information) unless explicitly required for a contractual purpose and subject to appropriate safeguards.
  </p>

  <h2>6. International Transfers</h2>
  <p>
    Your data may be processed in the UAE, US, Europe, or other regions.
  </p>
  <p>
    We implement appropriate safeguards—such as encryption and Standard Contractual Clauses (SCCs)—to ensure lawful, secure cross-border transfers.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Data Security &amp; Retention</h2>
  <p>
    We use technical and organizational measures—encryption, access controls, and audits—to protect data against loss or misuse.
  </p>
  <p>
    Data is retained only as long as necessary for its purpose or as required by law, after which it is securely deleted or anonymized.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Your Rights</h2>
  <p>
    Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have rights to:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Access your data.</li>
    <li>Correct inaccuracies.</li>
    <li>Request erasure.</li>
    <li>Restrict or object to processing.</li>
    <li>Receive data portability.</li>
    <li>Withdraw consent.</li>
    <li>Lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority (UAE Data Office or EU DPA).</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>California Residents:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Right to Know and Access.</li>
    <li>Right to Delete.</li>
    <li>Right to Opt-Out of Sale/Sharing (we do not sell personal data).</li>
    <li>Right to Non-Discrimination.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    To exercise these rights, contact our Data Protection Officer:
  </p>
  <p>
    Email: <a href="mailto:privacy@auxodata.com">privacy@auxodata.com</a>
  </p>

  <h2>9. Children's Data</h2>
  <p>
    Our Site and services are not directed at children under 16.
  </p>
  <p>
    We do not knowingly collect data from minors.
  </p>
  <p>
    If data is collected inadvertently, contact us for deletion.
  </p>
  <p>
    We take reasonable steps to ensure your data is accurate and up-to-date. You can contact us at any time to correct or update your information.
  </p>

  <h2>10. Policy Updates</h2>
  <p>
    We may revise this Policy periodically. Updates will appear on this page with a new "Last Updated" date. Continued use of our Site or services constitutes acceptance of the updated Policy.
  </p>

  <h2>11. Contact Us</h2>
  <p>
    For questions or privacy-related requests, contact our Data Protection Officer:
  </p>
  <p>
    Email: <a href="mailto:privacy@auxodata.com">privacy@auxodata.com</a>
  </p>

  <LegalContact intro="If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us at:" />
</LegalLayout>

